deck: Owlwoman is a raptor themed high tech character who appeared in the pages of Miracleman comic.
description:
Creation

Owlwoman is a character developed in the pages of Miracleman comic which was produced by Charleston Comics. She was created by Alan Moore and illustrated by Alan Davis.

History

In the time shortly after his battle with Miracleman the defeated Big Ben is shocked with what he see's in the Zarathustra bunker. Dismissing the truth and going further into his psychosis and rejects reality.In Big Ben’s version of events Jack Ketch and Owlwoman are colleagues from the Bulldog Brigade who arrive. Big Ben believes that Jack Ketch had told him how the red rogue had used a brain beam to make him to doubt his own identity. Big Ben allows Owlwoman to place an ultra-vest which she brings from her mountain fortress which would drain off the harmful mind-clouding radiation.

This is not the case however as in reality. Owlwoman and Jack Ketch are bureaucrats, serving the British state and its secret superhuman testing and its classified infrastructure.They are not the teamates and fellow heroes that Big Ben imagines are using a ultra-vest to disperse the mind controlling agent in his system. However she and the other doctor are actually using a straight jacket to secure him. Big Ben's delusion makes him believe the female doctor as Owlwoman.

Big Ben’s version of events in which he continues seeing himself as a super-hero even as the two doctors take him away. He also believes they escort him towards a waiting "Owlcar", which is actually a delivery truck. Big Ben totally believes that thanks to his delaying tactics they had been able to prevent Molotov escaping with the death ray. The two doctors, "Owlwoman" and "JackKetch" than depart into a highway back to their base to re-indoctrinate Big Ben.

Powers and Abilities

Owlwoman would have had several technically sophisticated gadgets and devices. She would be a great intellect, and apparent good combative. This however was not truly in existence as the woman Big Ben imagined to be Owlwoman was actually a plain, regular woman.

Appearance

Her large, circular glasses become the goggles in Owlwoman’s mask. Her lab coat becomes a cape. Her black vest morphs into a red and bright blue color pattern on her super-hero costume. Her circular belt buckle becomes a circular decoration on her torso.

Equipment and Paraphernalia

Owlwoman has an eccentric, streamlined vehicle called an Owlcar, which looks like it’s levitating slightly off the ground and doesn’t have any visible wheels.

She is a owl theme-based super-heroine with copious gadgets, including vehicles and a themed mountain fortress.
name: Owlwoman

deck: The King of the teddy bears and friend of Sally Sonic
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Barnabus, the Teddy Bear King. He was presumably the hereditary king of the teddy bear kingdom.

Creation

Barnabus was created by Grant Morrison and Yanick Paquette. He made his first appearance in Seven Soldiers: Bulleteer #4.

Major Story Arcs

Seven Soldiers of Victory

Barnabus accompanied young Sally Sonic on many fantastical missions before dying, possibly following a battle.

Powers and Abilities

Barnabus is a living teddy bear who appears to be made of stuffing; how he is animate is unknown. He appears to be capable of flight.
name: Teddy Bear King

deck: A criminal who manipulated Sally Sonic
description:
Origin

A criminal, Dennis and his brother were imprisoned by Judge Smart for their crimes. When his brother died in prison, Dennis swore to seek revenge on the Smart family. Upon leaving prison he acquired Vitamin X, which gave him superpowers, and took part in the Second World War as Vitaman.

Creation

Vitaman was created by Grant Morrison and Yanick Paquette. He made his first appearance in Seven Soldiers: Bulleteer #4.

Major Story Arcs

Seven Soldiers of Victory

Living in London, he encounters Sally Sonic, the daughter of Judge Smart, who, due to her immortality, appears to be permanently a teen. He seduces her by promising they will fight crime together, and slowly begins to manipulate her. He coerces her into getting involved in sex work, sells her for illegal fights, and gets her addicted to drugs. He eventually dies, but not before completely breaking Sally.

Powers and Abilities

Vitaman is superhumanly strong.
name: Vitaman

deck: One of the Baroness Paula Von Gunther's slave girls
description:
In Wonder Woman #3 (1943) when Wonder Woman returned to paradise island for what she described as amazon Christmas Baroness Paula Von Gunther had Keela stow away on the invisible plain. Once on the island she tried and failed to kill wonder woman before stealing a magic girdle from Queen Hippolyta. The girdle allowed her to out run and out fight Wonder Woman, taking her hostage until she was surprised by Etta Candy.

Once subdued it was revealed one of Keela’s bracelets had a radio tracker in it that was leading a Japanese battleship with the baroness on it to the island. The Japanese were easily pushed back and their ship destroyed by Steve Trevor, who was conveniently flying over looking for them.

The baroness and several of her slave girls made it to the island and were quickly captured. While Keela’s fate isn’t stated it can be assumed that she was sent to the nearby reform island with the rest of slave girls.
name: Keela
